## **3. Fetching Data from an API**

Most real apps depend on **external data**.

### **Correct Pattern**

```js
useEffect(() => {
  async function fetchData() {
    const res = await fetch(url);
    const data = await res.json();
    setState(data);
  }
  fetchData();
}, []);
```

---

### **Why Fetch Inside `useEffect`?**

• Runs after initial render
• Prevents blocking UI
• Aligns with React lifecycle

Never fetch data directly inside JSX or during render.

