## **5. Component Extraction — Why and When**

As apps grow, components get messy.

### **Symptoms You Need Extraction**

• `App.jsx` > 200 lines
• Repeated JSX
• Mixed responsibilities

---

### **Component Roles**

| Component | Responsibility     |
| --------- | ------------------ |
| App       | Owns state & logic |
| TaskList  | Renders list       |
| TaskItem  | Renders one item   |

---

## **6. Props: Data Flow Between Components**

Props are how data flows **downward**.

```jsx
<TaskItem task={task} onDelete={handleDelete} />
```

### **Rules of Props**

• Read-only
• Parent owns state
• Child triggers callbacks

---

### **Callback Pattern**

```js
function TaskItem({ task, onDelete }) {
  return <button onClick={() => onDelete(task.id)}>Delete</button>;
}
```

Child doesn’t delete — it **requests** deletion.

